<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1762,2042]" pageId="2" pageNumber="558">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1762,1789]" pageId="2" pageNumber="558">Description.</emphasis>
Male 
<typeStatus box="[366,468,1763,1789]" pageId="2" pageNumber="558">holotype</typeStatus>
. Integument mostly yellowish-brown, except for elytral bands and following somewhat dark brown areas: frons and part of dorsum of head; scape, pedicel; apex of antennomeres III-XI; anterior margin of pronotum, and behind dark band bordering; one longitudinal band on each side of pronotum, from anterior to posterior margin; inferior suface of pro- and mesofemora clubs; base of metafemoral club; metatibiae and metatarsi; meso- and metasternum; sparse setae-bearing punctures on dorsal surface of elytra; line of smaller punctures on epipleuron.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1762,2042]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,153,720]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="559" pageId="2" pageNumber="558">Elytral dark areas disposed as follows: first band transverse, placed slightly behind scutellum, from suture to epipleural margin; second band subparallel to first, slightly oblique from lateral margin to near suture, then strongly oblique backward toward suture; first and second bands merge together along epipleuron; Subtriangular macula placed after middle, from suture to epipleural margin (projected forward along epipleural margin),; fourth band preapical, curved, with convexity directed backward, from suture to epipleural margin, where it is fused to the projection of subtriangular macula.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,153,720]" box="[199,751,297,323]" pageId="3" pageNumber="559">Elytra somewhat widened toward the apical area.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,153,720]" pageId="3" pageNumber="559">
<typeStatus box="[199,303,333,359]" pageId="3" pageNumber="559">Holotype</typeStatus>
measurements (in mm): maximal width of pronotum: 1.14; length of prothorax: 1.20; humeral width: 1.32; maximal width of elytra: 1.68; elytral length: 3.66; total length: 5.46.
</paragraph>
