<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,153,720]" pageId="3" pageNumber="559">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,467,548,575]" pageId="3" pageNumber="559">Taxonomic discussion:</emphasis>
resembling 
<taxonomicName authority="Zubarán, 2020" authorityName="Zubarán" authorityYear="2020" box="[604,815,549,575]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Obrium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="559" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trilobatum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[604,815,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="559">Obrium trilobatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[821,907,549,575]" pageId="3" pageNumber="559" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the pattern of dark elytral bands, but the two species can be distinguished by large and wide scores in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zubarán" authorityYear="2020" box="[794,932,585,611]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Obrium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="559" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mimicum">
<emphasis box="[794,932,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="559">O. mimicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and small and narrow in 
<emphasis box="[1228,1388,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="559">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zubarán" authorityYear="2020" box="[1228,1384,585,611]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Obrium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="559" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trilobatum">O. trilobatum</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and the shape of the second and third elitral bands.
</paragraph>
